# Enterprise Application Standards v1.0
> These rules are MANDATORY. Apply them to every file you generate or modify.

## DATABASE RULES

### Naming (DB-01)
- [MUST] snake_case for ALL table and column names
- [MUST] Tables are plural nouns: `users`, `orders`, `line_items`
- [MUST] Primary keys named `id` (UUID v4 or BIGSERIAL)
- [MUST] Foreign keys: `<referenced_table>_id`
- [SHOULD] Booleans prefixed: `is_`, `has_`, `can_`, `should_`
- [SHOULD] Timestamps: `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`
- [AVOID] Abbreviations: no `usr`, `acct`, `txn`
- [AVOID] SQL reserved words as column names

### Schema (DB-02)
- [MUST] Every table has `created_at`, `updated_at` (auto-managed)
- [MUST] Soft deletes use `deleted_at` nullable timestamp — NOT `is_deleted`
- [MUST] No business logic in database triggers
- [AVOID] JSON blobs as primary data in relational tables

### Migrations (DB-04)
- [MUST] All schema changes via versioned migration files
- [MUST] Migrations are backward compatible (expand-contract)
- [MUST] Never rename/drop a column in a single deployment
- [AVOID] Bundling data migrations with schema migrations

---

## API RULES

### Endpoints (API-01)
- [MUST] Plural nouns: `/users`, `/orders`, `/products`
- [MUST] Correct HTTP verbs: GET/POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE
- [MUST] NO verbs in paths — `/getUser` is forbidden
- [SHOULD] Max 2 levels of nesting: `/users/{id}/orders`

### Responses (API-02)
- [MUST] Envelope: `{ "data": ..., "meta": {...}, "errors": [] }`
- [MUST] Timestamps in ISO 8601 UTC: `2024-01-15T10:30:00Z`
- [MUST] Empty arrays `[]` — never `null` for arrays
- [MUST] Versioned URL prefix: `/v1/`, `/v2/`
- [AVOID] Different response shapes for the same resource

### Errors (API-04)
- [MUST] Error body: `{ "code": "...", "message": "...", "details": [...], "request_id": "..." }`
- [MUST] NEVER return HTTP 200 with error content in body
- [AVOID] Exposing internal stack traces in API responses

### Security (API-03)
- [MUST] All endpoints require auth unless explicitly marked public
- [MUST] JWT: 15min access token, 7d refresh token
- [MUST] Rate limiting on all endpoints
- [MUST] NEVER log request bodies containing PII or credentials
- [AVOID] Auth tokens in URL query parameters

---

## FRONTEND / UI RULES

### Components (UI-01)
- [MUST] Single-responsibility — one concern per component
- [MUST] No business logic in UI components — use hooks/services
- [MUST] TypeScript types for ALL props (no `any`)
- [SHOULD] Atomic design: atoms → molecules → organisms → pages
- [AVOID] Inline styles — use design tokens and utility classes

### Design System (UI-02)
- [MUST] Approved design system components for standard UI elements
- [MUST] Colors/typography/spacing via design tokens only
- [MUST] Dark mode support for all new components
- [AVOID] Third-party UI libraries outside the approved list

### Accessibility (UI-03)
- [MUST] WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
- [MUST] All interactive elements keyboard navigable
- [MUST] All images have descriptive alt text

### State (UI-04)
- [MUST] Server state via React Query or SWR — NOT Redux
- [AVOID] Prop drilling more than 2 levels deep

---

## BACKEND RULES

### Service Layer (BE-01)
- [MUST] Business logic in service layer — not controllers or models
- [MUST] Services are stateless
- [MUST] DB access only through repository/DAO layer
- [AVOID] Circular service dependencies

### Logging (BE-02)
- [MUST] Structured JSON logs: `{ level, timestamp, service, trace_id, message }`
- [MUST] NEVER log PII, credentials, or payment data
- [AVOID] Empty catch blocks (exception swallowing)

### Config (BE-03)
- [MUST] All config via environment variables
- [MUST] Secrets in secret manager (AWS SM / Vault) — NEVER in code
- [MUST] Validate all config at startup — fail fast
- [AVOID] Committing .env files to version control

### Testing (BE-04)
- [MUST] 80% unit test coverage for service layer
- [MUST] Integration tests for all API endpoints
- [MUST] Tests must be deterministic — no flaky tests

---

## ARCHITECTURE RULES

### Boundaries (ARCH-01)
- [MUST] Services own their data — no cross-service DB access
- [MUST] Cross-service communication via APIs or message queues
- [AVOID] Shared databases between independent services

### Resilience (ARCH-02)
- [MUST] Circuit breakers on all external service calls
- [MUST] Idempotent message consumers
- [AVOID] Synchronous chains longer than 3 services

### Security (ARCH-03)
- [MUST] Zero-trust — all internal traffic authenticated
- [MUST] mTLS for service-to-service in production

### Observability (ARCH-04)
- [MUST] OpenTelemetry distributed tracing on all services
- [MUST] Alerts on error rate, P99 latency, saturation
- [AVOID] Manual dashboard creation — all observability as code

---

## HOW TO APPLY THESE RULES

When generating code:
1. Apply all [MUST] rules without exception or asking
2. Apply [SHOULD] rules by default; comment if deviating
3. Never produce patterns marked [AVOID]
4. Use rule IDs in comments when enforcing: `// API-02-01`
5. When reviewing code, flag violations with rule IDs

Detailed standards: `.ai/standards/` directory
